getRecoverDigest(address,uint256,address.details: Uses `_hashTypedDataSansChainId` (chain-agnostic domain separator) so the domain      does NOT include chainId. Instead, chainId is embedded in the struct hash.

isInitialized(address).details: Returns if the module was already initialized for a provided smartaccount

onInstall(bytes).details: data format: abi.encode(address mainAccount, address userGuardian, address externalGuardian, uint8 guardianThreshold)      Idempotent  silently returns if already initialized (supports multi-type install: validator + executor).

onUninstall(bytes).details: Idempotent  silently returns if already cleared (supports multi-type uninstall).

recoverWithGuardian(address,uint256,addr.details: Callable by anyone (permissionless). Signature format depends on the account's threshold:      - threshold=1: `[type_byte][sig]` where type_byte is `0x00` (user) or `0x01` (external)      - threshold=2: `[user_sig_len: uint16][user_sig][external_sig]` (both must sign)

params._externalGuardian: Address of the external guardian (address(0) to clear)
params._userGuardian: Address of the user guardian (address(0) to clear)

getMainAccount(address).notice: Returns the main account linked to an app account (address(0) if not installed)

getRecoverDigest(address,uint256,address.notice: Computes the EIP-712 recovery digest for off-chain or on-chain verification

guardianConfig(address).notice: Returns the full guardian configuration for an app account

guardianThreshold(address).notice: Returns the effective guardian threshold for an app account (defaults to 1 if unset)

mainValidator().notice: The main OneAuthValidator that holds credentials and computes EIP-712 domains

nonceUsed(address,uint256).notice: Checks whether a specific recovery nonce has been consumed for an app account

onInstall(bytes).notice: Install the app validator for the caller's account

recoverWithGuardian(address,uint256,addr.notice: Recovers an app account by changing which main account it delegates to

setGuardianConfig(address,address,uint8).notice: Set or change the guardian configuration for the caller's app account
